<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 2:16PM PDT  by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Baker
County through 245 PM PDT...
At 215 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Rock Creek, or 11 miles southwest of North Powder,
moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Anthony Lakes Ski Area and Elkhorn Peak.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
